Unfortunately, the web site
http://orbitcpp.sourceforge.net
is more or less abandoned and unmaintained.

If you have questions specific to the new IDL to C++0x mapping,
atm the best place to go is
http://www.orbzone.org/forum/70

Later, the new standard will be published at the OMG, see
http://www.omg.org/techprocess/meetings/schedule/IDL_to_C++0x_Language_Mapping_RFP.html

Following people have been maintainers or major contributors to
the original ORBit-C++ project:

